Together with &lt;a href="http://ir.cis.udel.edu/~carteret/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Ben Carterette&lt;/a>, &lt;a href="http://www.dei.unipd.it/~ferro/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Nicola Ferro&lt;/a>, and &lt;a href="https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=p53Ht7UAAAAJ" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Norbert Fuhr&lt;/a>, I co-organized the seminar on the &lt;a href="https://www.dagstuhl.de/23031" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Frontiers of Information Access Experimentation for Research and Education&lt;/a>.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>It has been a great week. And I am very happy about the work we have accomplished and the inspiring discussions. I have learned a lot. The final report is indeed more or less done and only needs a bit of polishing before we can publish it. Thank you to all participants for your great contributions!&lt;/p>
&lt;p>I am, of course, also very happy that we have invited the right people to also have fun in the music room ;-)&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Dagstuhl seminar next week</title><link>https://chbeu.github.io/post/20230113_dagstuhl/</link><pubDate>Fri, 13 Jan 2023 02:00:06 +0200</pubDate><guid>https://chbeu.github.io/post/20230113_dagstuhl/</guid><description>&lt;p>I am looking forward to spend next week at Schloss Dagstuhl. Together with &lt;a href="http://ir.cis.udel.edu/~carteret/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Ben Carterette&lt;/a>, &lt;a href="http://www.dei.unipd.it/~ferro/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Nicola Ferro&lt;/a>, and &lt;a href="http://www.is.inf.uni-due.de/staff/fuhr.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Norbert Fuhr&lt;/a>, I am co-organizer of the seminar on the &lt;a href="https://www.dagstuhl.de/23031" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Frontiers of Information Access Experimentation for Research and Education&lt;/a>.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>It will be an intense but&amp;mdash;for sure&amp;mdash;also an enjoyable and productive week.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>CHIIR 2020 tutorial paper on multi-method evaluation is online</title><link>https://chbeu.github.io/post/_posts_wordpress/2020-03-14-chiir-2020-tutorial-paper-on-multi-method-evaluation-is-online/</link><pubDate>Sat, 14 Mar 2020 10:36:37 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://chbeu.github.io/post/_posts_wordpress/2020-03-14-chiir-2020-tutorial-paper-on-multi-method-evaluation-is-online/</guid><description>&lt;p>While &lt;a href="https://sigir.org/chiir2020/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">CHIIR 2020&lt;/a> had to be cancelled due to the current global situation with Covid-19, the paper accompanying the tutorial on multi-method evaluation (that I would have held there) is published.&lt;/p>
